                        <text>A patent is like a special certificate or permission slip that inventors get when they create something new and unique, like a super cool gadget or a fantastic machine. It&apos;s a way for them to say, &quot;Hey, I made this first, and I want to protect my idea for a while.&quot; When someone gets a patent, it means they have exclusive rights to make and sell their invention for a certain amount of time, usually around 20 years. This gives them a chance to show off their amazing invention and maybe even make some money from it. But in return, they have to share the details of how it works with everyone else. So, when the time is up, others can learn from it and make similar things.</text>
